<h1>Complaint Entry Module &mdash; Database Table Field Documentation</h1>

<p class="meta">
<strong>Project:</strong> Complaint Management (Dealer Portal)<br>
<strong>Module:</strong> Complaint Entry<br>
<strong>Page:</strong> new_complaint.php<br>
<strong>Database:</strong> complaint_management<br>
<strong>Generated:</strong> June 2026
</p>

<div class="note">
This document describes all database tables and fields used by the <strong>Complaint Entry</strong> module,
including the main complaint record, optional assignment at registration, activity logging, and related workflow tables.
</div>

<h2>1. Overview</h2>
<p>When a user submits a new complaint from <strong>Complaint Entry</strong>, the system:</p>
<ol>
<li>Inserts a record into the <code>complaints</code> table.</li>
<li>Optionally inserts an assignment into <code>complaint_assignments</code> if <em>Assign To</em> is selected.</li>
<li>Logs activity into <code>complaint_activity_logs</code>.</li>
<li>Sets initial status to <strong>Open (1)</strong> or <strong>In Progress (2)</strong> if assigned during entry.</li>
</ol>

<h2>2. Primary Table: complaints</h2>
<p>Stores the main complaint registration details entered on the Complaint Entry form.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th>Data Type</th>
<th>Required</th>
<th>Form Label</th>
<th>Description / Business Rules</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>id</code></td>
<td>Integer (Auto)</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>&mdash;</td>
<td>Primary key. Auto-generated complaint ID displayed as #ID in lists and details.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>fab_number</code></td>
<td>Varchar</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Fab Number</td>
<td>Machine fabric number. Selected from invoice search (Select2). Must exist in dealer portal invoice details (<code>ln_invoice</code>). JavaScript and server validation required.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>customer_name</code></td>
<td>Varchar</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Customer Name</td>
<td>Name of the customer reporting the complaint. Maximum 200 characters on form.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>street_1</code></td>
<td>Varchar(255)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Street 1</td>
<td>Primary address line (house / building / street). Maximum 255 characters.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>street_2</code></td>
<td>Varchar(255)</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Street 2</td>
<td>Secondary address line (area / landmark). Optional. Maximum 255 characters.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>pincode</code></td>
<td>Varchar(20)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Pincode</td>
<td>6-digit Indian pincode. Selected from postcode master. Auto-fills city, district, and state.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>city</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>City</td>
<td>City name. Auto-populated from pincode lookup. Read-only on form.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>district</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>District</td>
<td>District name. Auto-populated from pincode lookup. Read-only on form.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>state</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>State</td>
<td>State name. Auto-populated from pincode lookup. Read-only on form.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>customer_address</code></td>
<td>Text / Varchar</td>
<td>Legacy</td>
<td>&mdash;</td>
<td>Legacy single-line address field retained for older records. New entries use structured address fields (<code>street_1</code> to <code>state</code>). Display falls back to this field when <code>street_1</code> is empty.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>complaint_description</code></td>
<td>Text</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Complaint Description</td>
<td>Detailed description of the issue reported by the customer.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>status</code></td>
<td>Smallint / Integer</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Status</td>
<td>Complaint workflow status. Set automatically on insert. See Section 5 for status values.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>added_by</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>&mdash;</td>
<td>User ID of the person who registered the complaint. Currently stored as system user ID.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>username</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>&mdash;</td>
<td>Logged-in username from session (<code>$_SESSION['usr_name']</code>). Used to filter complaints by creator.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>created_at</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Created At</td>
<td>Date and time when the complaint was registered. Set by database default.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>updated_at</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Updated At</td>
<td>Date and time of last update. Updated during assignment, service update, closure, and delete operations.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>deleted_at</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>&mdash;</td>
<td>Soft delete timestamp. When set, the complaint is hidden from lists. Physical record is not removed.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>3. Complaint Entry Form Fields (UI Mapping)</h2>
<p>Fields shown on the <strong>New Complaint</strong> form and their mapping to database columns.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Section</th>
<th>Form Field Name</th>
<th>UI Label</th>
<th>Maps To Table.Column</th>
<th>Validation</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>fab_number</code></td>
<td>Fab Number</td>
<td>complaints.fab_number</td>
<td>Required; must exist in invoice master</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>customer_name</code></td>
<td>Customer Name</td>
<td>complaints.customer_name</td>
<td>Required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>street_1</code></td>
<td>Street 1</td>
<td>complaints.street_1</td>
<td>Required; max 255 chars</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>street_2</code></td>
<td>Street 2</td>
<td>complaints.street_2</td>
<td>Optional; max 255 chars</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>pincode</code></td>
<td>Pincode</td>
<td>complaints.pincode</td>
<td>Required; exactly 6 digits</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>city</code></td>
<td>City</td>
<td>complaints.city</td>
<td>Required; auto-filled from pincode</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>district</code></td>
<td>District</td>
<td>complaints.district</td>
<td>Required; auto-filled from pincode</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Customer Information</td>
<td><code>state</code></td>
<td>State</td>
<td>complaints.state</td>
<td>Required; auto-filled from pincode</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Complaint Details</td>
<td><code>complaint_description</code></td>
<td>Complaint Description</td>
<td>complaints.complaint_description</td>
<td>Required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Assignment (Optional)</td>
<td><code>assign_complaint</code></td>
<td>Assign To</td>
<td>complaint_assignments.assign_complaint</td>
<td>Optional at entry; if provided, status becomes In Progress</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Assignment (Optional)</td>
<td><code>remarks</code></td>
<td>Remarks</td>
<td>complaint_assignments.remarks</td>
<td>Optional; max 500 characters</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>4. Related Table: complaint_assignments</h2>
<p>Created during Complaint Entry when <em>Assign To</em> is selected, or later via manual assignment.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th>Data Type</th>
<th>Required</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>id</code></td>
<td>Integer (Auto)</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Primary key for assignment record.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>complaint_id</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Foreign key referencing <code>complaints.id</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>assign_complaint</code></td>
<td>Varchar</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Name or label of the assignee (DSE/LSE/engineer).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>assigned_to</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Assignee user ID (system reference).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>assign_complaint_datetime</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>Date and time when the complaint was assigned.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>remarks</code></td>
<td>Text</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>Assignment remarks entered during registration or reassignment. Max 500 characters.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>assigned_by</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>User ID of the person who performed the assignment.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>created_at</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Record creation timestamp.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>is_service_updated</code></td>
<td>Boolean / Flag</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Indicates whether a service update has been recorded against this assignment.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>username</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Auto</td>
<td>Logged-in username who created the assignment.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>5. Complaint Status Values</h2>
<p>Stored in <code>complaints.status</code>. Managed by <code>includes/complaint_status.php</code>.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Status ID</th>
<th>Status Label</th>
<th>When Set</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>Open</td>
<td>Default when complaint is registered without assignment.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td>In Progress</td>
<td>When complaint is assigned during entry or via manual assignment.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>Pending With HO</td>
<td>After service update is submitted by assigned engineer.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>4</td>
<td>Re-Open</td>
<td>When closure is marked as No and complaint is reassigned.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>5</td>
<td>Resolved</td>
<td>When closure is marked as Yes after service update.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>6. Activity Log Table: complaint_activity_logs</h2>
<p>Automatically populated when a complaint is created, assigned, updated, or closed.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th>Data Type</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>id</code></td>
<td>Integer (Auto)</td>
<td>Primary key.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>complaint_id</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>Reference to <code>complaints.id</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>activity_type</code></td>
<td>Varchar</td>
<td>Activity category: Created, Assignment, Reassignment, Service Update, Closure, Status Change, Deleted.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>activity_description</code></td>
<td>Text</td>
<td>Human-readable activity detail shown on complaint timeline.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>user_id</code></td>
<td>Integer</td>
<td>User ID associated with the activity.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>username</code></td>
<td>Varchar(100)</td>
<td>Logged-in username who performed the action.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>created_at</code></td>
<td>Timestamp</td>
<td>Activity timestamp.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>7. Downstream Workflow Tables (Post Entry)</h2>
<p>These tables are not part of the Complaint Entry form but are linked after assignment and service workflow.</p>

<h3>7.1 complaint_service_updates</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
<tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>complaint_id</code></td><td>Linked complaint</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>assignment_id</code></td><td>Linked assignment record</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>customer_visit_date</code></td><td>Date of customer site visit</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>complaint_action_taken</code></td><td>Actions performed during visit</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>part_replaced</code></td><td>Spare part replacement details (optional)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>service_report</code></td><td>Uploaded service report file name(s)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>created_by</code></td><td>User who submitted service update</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>created_at</code> / <code>updated_at</code></td><td>Timestamps</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>username</code></td><td>Logged-in username</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>7.2 complaint_closures</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Field Name</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
<tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>Primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>complaint_id</code></td><td>Linked complaint</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>call_closure</code></td><td>Yes or No</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>closure_remarks</code></td><td>Required when call_closure = Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>reassignment_details</code></td><td>Remarks when call_closure = No (reassignment)</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>closed_by</code></td><td>User who closed the complaint</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>created_at</code></td><td>Closure timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>username</code></td><td>Logged-in username</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>8. Validation Summary (Complaint Entry)</h2>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Field</th>
