<td>Required; max 255</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Street 2</td>
<td>Max 255</td>
<td>Max 255</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Pincode</td>
<td>Required; 6 digits</td>
<td>Required; 6 digits</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>City / District / State</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Complaint Description</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>Required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Remarks</td>
<td>Max 500</td>
<td>Max 500</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>9. List View Columns (Complaint Entry Grid)</h2>
<p>The Complaint Entry listing page displays the following columns from the <code>complaints</code> table:</p>
<ul>
<li>ID</li>
<li>Fab Number</li>
<li>Customer Name</li>
<li>Customer Address (formatted from street, city, district, state, pincode)</li>
<li>Complaint Description</li>
<li>Status (label, not raw ID)</li>
<li>Created At</li>
<li>Actions (View, Assign, Delete)</li>
</ul>

